apparently Scartazzini (comm. to this verse). Most modern commentators
also cite it, but, like Scartazzini, without noting that Virgil is
not referring to the Red Sea. If he is in fact citing the ^Aeneid~,
Dante either makes the same mistake his modern commentators make or
else forces the passage out of context, and has Augustus establishing
his dominion over that most propitious part of the Mediterranean world,
where Christ became flesh, as part of the ^plenitudo temporis~ (see the
